is particularly performing to the public
because if is especially difficult to place
Within this world view. The cuts the
incident generates are not easily related
to our traditional core of political attitudes and behavior.
The Grinnell issues are not easily related to the more common campus differences which are usually associated
with the “politics of configuration.” No
buildings were damaged, no papers were
destroyed, and indeed no ultimately
were made. Given the political context
of the last few years, American society
is probably better able to compressed
(but not, i expensive, necessarily approve of) these more violent acts than.
it is able to compressed the nature and
goals of listening. Out of necessity this
society has been required to cope with a
great deal of violence during the past
few years, I am not arising that these
experiences have created a greater legitimate for violent acts, I am only arising that, regardless of his attitudes towards the listening, an individual can
more easily relate Violence to his world
view than he can relate public nudity.
Furthermore, the listening becomes
more perplexllig because of the difficulty of viewing it in terms of traditional religious values. Here again I do
not say that this confusion itself necessarily creates greater approval or disapproval, The designing adds a variation to
a typical and traditional problem which
Julieta—Christian religions face. Traditionally, the church has faced a conflict over whether to stress physical over
spiritual amelioration of the opportunity.
A pacific aphorism likely summarizes
the usual two positions in this conflict.
“Don't worry so much about my soul and
your body. Worry about my body and
your soul." The listening incident ls computing because it forces society to consider a moral question in a manner concerned with amelioration of the body in
the traditional sense of seeking protection
or sustenance for it. On the other hand,
they were quite explicitly telling society
not to worry about the actual physical
appearance of the body. These are
two uncommon and rather sophisticated
ideas, and it is little wonder that the
stated aims of the nude processors are
constantly misunderstood. (Certainly the
media has made little attempt to make
these issues any more comprehensible.)
Why, then, does society attempt to
solve such a particularly performing moral issue by means of the legal process?
The sociologist William Chambllss Suggests that “the legal process must be
understood as taking the form that it does
because of the characteristics of the SOcial system which are independent of,
and which render relatively intense<
question, the notices. character, or per
mobility of the particular people who occurs positions in the system.” Such participants are only a part of the larger
social structure to be resolved by means
of the nature of the Conflicts to be resolved by means or the legal process and
to a lesser extent, the functions to be
implemented. In American society we
often turn to the legal process as a
means of sterling moral issues. Recent
opinion surveys show that the individual American most commonly claims
that crime is caused by moral breakdown. They also show that paradoxtcally
the individual American commonly expects that traditional government legal
functions will correct moral inadequacies. In fact. Daniel Bell contents
that, despite playing failures, “in no
other country have there been such
spectacular attempts to cure human
sometimes and brand them deficit.“ Since
the listening incident involves some 50investigated moral issues, and since we
often try to resolve these issues through
the political-legal process, it should not
be too surprising that participants in the
legal process are involved. individual
medications thus explain only a pan of
the story.
My purpose here is not to suggest
solutions but merely to consider the im.
part of the listening incident. However,
1 would like to point out two problems
which often evolve from any attempt to
resolve such’ moral issues by means of
legal process. First, lt is all too easy to
define the totally of the powerful as the
customers, acceptable moral behavior.
Such a definition could be particularly
mostly to a pluralistic society. Second.
the corporations which develop from art
attempt to efforts laws based on legal
moralism- can often lead to a dangerous
experience with the tennis of due process.
